A yearly subscription is refundable within 14 days of purchase and includes a 365-day membership. Land Bank is one of several struggling state-owned companies that have required government handouts, straining the public purse at a time of weak economic growth and leading to credit rating downgrades into “junk” status. It said last week that it was working on a new debt restructuring plan after the Treasury declined to provide a partial government guarantee. The Treasury said an assessment had shown that further guarantees were an inappropriate instrument and equity was required. More information on the R7 billion required by the bank would be made available during the 2021 Budget, which is due in February, it said, adding: “In its role as shareholder, government’s main instrument of support is equity.”